The boundaries depicted are "representations only"  Users should refer to regulations and on site information as to their exact location. </abstract>       <purpose>This application was designed to provide some basic resource information about Arkansas Game and Fish Commission facilities</purpose>       <supplinf>An image service uses the spatial server image rendering capabilities. When GeoStor receives a request, a map is generated on the server, and the response is sent back as a JPG, PNG, or GIF image. A new map image is generated each time a client requests new information.  GeoStor image services may be used with ArcGIS products, as well as Open GIS Consortium web map service (WMS) compliant viewers.</supplinf>     </descript>     <citation>       <citeinfo>
